[[Image:BlackDiamondCheeseLogo.jpg|right]]
'''Black Diamond Cheese Limited''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[cheese]] [[manufacturing]] company, established in [[1933]], by [[Robert F. Hart]].  Founded under the name "Belleville Cheddar Cheese Limited", its original purpose was to export aged Canadian cheddar to the [[United Kingdom|British]] market. 

It is owned by [[Parmalat]] of Canada, since [[1998]].  The subsidiary employs approximately 470 people at its factory in [[Belleville, Ontario]].

